main event: A civilian reported observing multiple highly illuminated unidentified objects maneuvering near Dayton, Ohio in early January 1964.
interesting points: The sighting occurred approximately 10 miles west of Dayton,The witness only called to report the sighting but did not provide further details later,The objects appeared to be maneuverable and seemed to rendezvous, The observation type was classified as Ground-Visual, The Air Force concluded that the objects could be balloons or aircraft but stated that essential data was missing for a definitive evaluation.
witness description: a civilian who lives about 10 miles north of Dayton
